			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Reasonable expected twist?<a name="27753"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 15 04 10:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>3 is fine.  That's normal and also ample -- I'm assuming the 3 are Muse, Marr and Zek/POV.  Doing Zek + POV is certainly handy, but doesn't add so much to the group's ability as to justify killing yourself over.  (OK, bad assumption :P.  At 21, it's not Muse, Marr &amp; Zek, but the point remains the same.  The 4th song, whatever it is, likely doesn't add enough marginal value to warrant the effort.)
<br />

<br />
Also, don't get all stressed out about the song count.  Sure, all other things being equal, more songs playing = more effective group.  But depending on your role in the group there may be other things for you to do that are more important than keeping 3 or 4 buffs going 24/7.  Examples:
<br />

<br />
* If you're pulling, the single best thing you can do to amplify group DPS is keep the group putting out DPS at all times.  If the group sits even 15 seconds between pulls, average DPS over, say, one LDON adventure will be much worse -- even with 4 songs playing full time during the fight -- that it would be if the bard is gone a lot (0 songs twisted) but always has a new pull ready to die when the old one drops.
<br />

<br />
* If you have a healer or a gating mob, chain mezzing it can stop a complete heal or a gate.  It's worth a whole heapa DPS not to have to kill the mob twice.
<br />

<br />
* I find that since I'm usually pulling, I'm also usually managing some tactical calls -- don't get too close to that door or adds will come etc.  Typing that kind of guidance costs me song twisting sometimes, but its worth it.
<br />

<br />
* Being sensible about where you fight -- fighting from behind the mob is far more important now that mobs can riposte for 1K.  I think it's much better for me to position right and stay positioned right -- even if it means I let a song drop while I reorient.
<br />

<br />
The point is that a bard who sometimes has 2, 1, or even 0 buffs in the group's buff window isn't necessarily doing a worse job than the bard who has 4 going.  Don't fixate on the song count.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
