				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Reasonable expected twist?<a name="27772"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 15 04 11:50 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The level 20 slow is also an AC debuff.  That means your melees will hit more, which is always helpful.
<br />

<br />
Take a look at Chant of Battle again.  Str just like Anthem -- no haste but Anthem wasn't much haste, and Chant gives AC.   Especially with an enchanter, Chant can be better than Anthem.
<br />

<br />
Clarity and/or Hymn are certainly good choices as well.
<br />

<br />
Have you found Reed's spreadsheet yet?  It's stickied at the top of this forum.  It will tell you exactly what your songs are doing and you can then make an informed choice about how to balance ac vs haste vs str vs atk etc etc.
<br />
</span></td>
