				<td colspan="2"><span>I can keep 4 &quot;almost&quot; up (one is always JUST dropping as it gets refreshed, I see it drop but group probably doesn't) -- 5 if I sneak Niv's in from my Breath of Harmony, it's an instaclick -- and have done so occasionally to show off (LOL), or in crisis situations. Mostly I feel happy if I&quot;m doing 3, that gives me plenty of time to swap instruments if needed, pay attention to my melee positioning, sneak in a tell or groupsay, etc etc. To do 4 I really have to do NOTHING else, 3 is pretty easy.
<br />

<br />
I have recently been pondering the utility of weaving 4 or 5 songs into a twist though.  For instance, when AE kiting I often do selos-hymn-cod-selos-ddd-cod if I get a bit hurt.  Out of every 5 ticks, hymn is up 3, and ddd is up three (sometimes 4 if the dot lands the right half of the &quot;tick&quot;). I feel this is much more effective than a straight three song twist in that situation.</span></td>
